<div id="block-views-news-block-our-priorities" class="block block-views first last odd">

    	  	  	    	<div class="block-title-wrapper"><h2 class="block__title block-title"><a href="/en/about-us/our-priorities" class="text">Latest News</a><a href="/en/about-us/our-priorities/rss" class="news-rss">RSS</a></h2></div>
	      
  <div class="view view-news view-id-news view-display-id-block_our_priorities view-dom-id-acce7542cc07d8c11f242148d4592273">
        
  
  
      <div class="view-content">
        <div class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first">
      
  <div class="views-field views-field-field-news-image">        <div class="field-content"><a href="/en/about-us/our-people/our-priorities/chief-science-officer"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://rsc-src.ca/sites/default/files/styles/thumbnail/public/images/RSC_Narrow_Black_Logo_9.png?itok=t_HiJtnW" width="131" height="101" alt="" title="Royal Society of Canada" /></a></div>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-title">        <span class="field-content"><a href="/en/about-us/our-people/our-priorities/chief-science-officer">Chief Science Officer</a></span>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-body">        <div class="field-content"><span class="created">4 March 2016</span><p>The Royal Society of Canada was approached by Minister of Science, the Honourable Kirsty Duncan, for advice on the role of the future Chief Science Officer (CSO) in Canada.¬†</p><p>The RSC‚Äôs response, prepared by the Committee on Expert Panels...</p></div>  </div>  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even">
      
